caption: Tied for the best sushi I’ve had in my life. Not much movement so it’s also pretty calm. 10/10 definitely recommend!

VERY GOOD sushi! Delicious and very fresh, handmade efficiently while you wait. The rolls are VERY good portions, especially for the price. Even to go, the presentation is so nice. Very friendly and genuine service. The miso soup is also very tasty. Loved it all!
The sushi and the chef ar amazing!!! This place is on of New Orleans best kept secrets.
I often meet people here to talk. The staff was very helpful and observant. This place has a good atmosphere.

I've been eating here for years and it's the best sushi for the best price anywhere in town. The service is great and they clearly care about the quality of their food. Thank you so much. I hope you open up soon.
Recommend. Pretty good sushi. No issues at all. Very kind service.

Had the lunch special and was pleasantly surprised. Came with soup, salad,  and 2 rolls. It was delicious and the service was great. Great views of the ocean as we ate made it even better.
Great food great price nice employees!!! We got the crunchy cali roll the rock n roll and the ninja roll soooo good!

Sushi was good, but the owner and cashier disagreed about whether they accept Discover Card. I ended up paying with cash, but the fact that there was even a debate was annoying (since it's not professional and I use Discover for everything; I'd never encountered a restaurant in New Orleans that doesn't accept it). I'm not sure I'll come back.
The sushi is very good and priced reasonably. I had similar sushi at other places that were way more expensive.

Let me start by saying I go here EVERYTIME I go to New Orleans without fail. This place has amazing food and staff. I wholeheartedly reccomend going if you are in the area. Don't miss out on this little hidden gem in the city.
If you work in the french quarter, this should be your lunch. Cheap, quality, and because its in the JAX food court, it will likely never have a long line.
Food was good until it made me sick just a couple hours later

Was walking around Jackson Square and stumbled upon a sushi bar in New Orleans, figured I would try it out. One of the best decisions I've made in my trip. Rolls were well made, and delicious, fish was fresh, and everything was made right in front of me. When I come back to New Orleans, I will be stopping by Jazz Sushi.
This place is amazing! The customer service was on point and the sushi is soooooo good. This is definitely the best sushi in New Orleans. It’s a hidden gem.
Great sushi. Great prices. I wish this was where I lived. I tried 4 different rolls. I'm surprised it wasn't more busy. The man and woman working there were very nice.
The food was good, but it took a long time and eating in a mall ain't all that. The poke bowl was very good. I guess I need some ambiance with my raw fish and this wasn't working for me.
First place I broke my sushi virgin. No one in the can top them. Fried salmon roll is my favorite! Great customer service.
The most inexpensive sushi I've ever had. And some of the most pure, delicious, and simple I've had. Totally worth eating here twice.
Truly a hidden gem! Overlooks the riverboats right on the quarter. The food was some of the best we've ever had. For the area, the prices can't be beat. Go to the food court and enjoy!

Restaurant is located in a mall food-court. Sushi affordable, good options, and staff very friendly. The only cons are the atmosphere and the obviously display of poor food handling. Cross-Contamination at its highest.

Delicious food. Good price. Free delivery! Portions were great. Miso soup had big chunks of tofo and the crispy crab roll was probably the best I've ever had. Spicy salmon roll was a generous portion. Food was delivered by bike and knocked around a bit, so it wasn't stellar looking, but didn't detract from the deliciousness. Would happily order again.
